Shakedown: A Most Excellent Tragicomedy of Glyph and Line.

Rosalind, keeper of references, agile of tongue across the Forest of Arden.

Horatio, plain witness of the household, holder of secrets.

Puck, swift messenger, who wears each room's colour and flies between them.

Hecate, witch-queen, who scours the underbelly of the page.

Lady Macbeth, mason of the block, who cuts the page into rooms.

Romeo, who pushes candidate substitutions like sunlit petals.

Juliet, night-star lyric, who lays final roses on the silver path.

Prospero, scribe and emitter, whose pronouncements close the work.



                    Act I: Wherein the witches sort raw matter into shelves and seals.
                    Scene I: Hecate shelves the known bargains.

[Enter Hecate and Rosalind]

Hecate:
 You are as rotten as a cat.

Hecate:
 Remember yourself.

Hecate:
 You are as rotten as the sum of the product of a normal little furry black cat and the sum
